Hey there! Great to meet you. I’m Addie, the Business Development Rep for BitSafe — the wrapped Bitcoin provider on Canton. Following up on our co-founder Aki’s message in the channel.

BitSafe (makers of iBTC) is launching CBTC, a wrapped Bitcoin on Canton.

CBTC was recently approved as a Featured App. Companies with CBTC credentials will be eligible to earn extra CantonCoins.

We’re starting with the Early Bird Holder License ($500/month, paid in CantonCoins via the Credential Utility). This license allows you to hold and transfer CBTC. Under the current reward structure, it provides meaningful earning potential.

Learn more: <https://hub.bitsafe.finance/cbtc-overview>
Join the waitlist: <https://form.typeform.com/to/esAv2IQz>

Let’s set up 30 minutes to discuss. Book time with me here: <https://calendly.com/addie-dlc/30min>

Common question:

Hey <@U05FZBDQ4RJ>, Thanks. But from what I saw on Canton whitepaper you earn rewards only when you utilise Synchronizer so how does holding a token use GSF?

Hi <@U06N5HZSU5P> - a common question! You're earning CantonCoin rewards from paying for a credential.

When you pay $6,000/yr, it's split out into 10-minute blocks that bill $0.11 each. Since we're a Featured App, they attach a featured app coupon that pays an additional $0.58 for each block.
[2:51 PM] Aki

The rewards arrive to us, and we distribute at the end of each month. Canton doesn't yet have an auto-distribute feature, so each app creator has to distribute them manually. We're building a script to calculate it by block height (edited)
